results.verbatimLocality: L'Ile du Lamantin, Niger River, bordering Parc W, Niger
results.occurrenceRemarks: Short (2.5 m) evergreen tree bearing grey-green bi-lobate leaves with palmate venation, and mature dark brown and twisted pods (ca. 3 x 20 cm). Growing on the flood plain between the open-air dining room and my cabin at Eco-Lodge Brousse on the "Island of the Manatees", in the River Niger, about 2 km north of the Park W Campsite (on the western bank of the river, in the northern portion of Parc W, in Niger on its frontiers with Benin and Burkina Faso). This is a very common tree of the more humid parts of the the Sahelian agro-ecological region, and the northern Sudanian agro-ecological region, and its pods are used to produce a brown dye that is used in local textile manufacture.
